The paper deals with communication systems and signal processing, which are typically covered under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of multiple antennas at the receivers falls under the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses optimization methods, which can be classified under the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
